<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-08-10T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-08-10T18:00:00-05:00" n="397" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d397">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2516a: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Chargé in France</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-08-10T19:00:00-04:00">August 10, 1936—7
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>304. A press report this afternoon from London states that the French
                                Government is preparing to invite the American Government to adhere
                                to the proposed European Pact of Non-intervention in the Spanish
                                civil war.</p>
                            <p>Please telegraph at once any information which you can obtain
                                respecting the correctness of this report. A similar telegram is
                                being sent to London.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Phillips</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>